The paper focuses on developing an algorithm for finding effective configurations for assistive robots to better reach task-relevant locations and handle task variation. This involves modeling the task, environment, and user, and implicitly handling error using representations of robot dexterity. These topics are closely related to the fields of robotics (cs.RO), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
